<paragraph id="0A691048FF8FFF8CFF6946CDFDB3FED5" blockId="9.[168,775,160,351]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="38A2CC5AFF8FFF8CFF6946CDFE2AFF32" bold="true" box="[168,420,160,184]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the group VII of 
<taxonomicName id="CDD66BCBFF8FFF8CFF2D46ACFDAEFF53" authority="(Borgmeier 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Borgmeier" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[236,544,193,217]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A2CC5AFF8FFF8CFF2D46ACFED5FF53" box="[236,347,193,217]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Megaselia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6E476DB9FF8FFF8CFEA646ACFD96FF53" author="Borgmeier T" box="[359,536,193,217]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" pagination="289 - 488" refId="ref10642" refString="Borgmeier T (1962) Versuch einer Uebersichtueber die neotropischen Megaselia - Arten, sowie neue oder wenig bekannte Phoriden verschiedener Gattungen (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica 5: 289 - 488." type="journal article" year="1962">Borgmeier 1962</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This is a very striking species, easily recognizable by the unique morphology of the asymmetrical hypopygium with 2 expanded lobes. Right lobe large, spoon shaped, hollowed out in the inside face; and left lobe smaller, bifurcated.
</paragraph>
